article.headline: Missouri St. 57, UC Irvine 48
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. -- Chris Cooks scored 16 points, including back-to-back 3-pointers late in the game, to lead Missouri State to a 57-48 win over UC Irvine in the Basketball Travelers Tip-Off Tournament. Missouri State (7-3) was ahead by only one at halftime Sunday, 27-26, and led just 42-40 with 8:03 left after a basket by UC Irvine's Kevin Bland. But the Bears pushed their lead to 51-44 with 3:27 left on three straight 3-pointers -- one from Justin Fuehrmeyer and two from Cooks. Missouri State finished with six straight free throws while UC Irvine (1-9) scored a field goal and two free throws in a game that saw five ties, eight lead changes and 26 turnovers. Both teams shot poorly from the field. Missouri State hit 35.3 percent on 18 of 51 while UC Irvine hit on 18 of 50 for 36 percent. Spencer Laurie added 10 for Missouri State. Bland led UC Irvine with 16 points.
